.TH MORSE(1),User Commands,MORSE(1)

.SH NAME
morse - translate text to morse code

.SH SYNOPSIS
morse [file ...]

.SH DESCRIPTION
The morse utility reads text from the specified files (or standard input if none are given) and prints the morse code equivalent to standard output.

Letters are separated by a single space. Words are separated by three spaces. Each input line produces one output line.

Supported characters: A-Z (case insensitive), 0-9, and the punctuation marks . , ? ! / = + -

Unrecognized characters are silently ignored.

.SH EXIT STATUS
The morse utility exits 0 on success, and >0 if an error occurs.

.SH EXAMPLES
Encode a string:

$ echo "hello world" | morse

Encode a file:

$ morse message.txt
